In the bicycle class held as the start event of the operation, a car-bicycle collision test was conducted = Tsuruoka City, Shoko Gakuen Driving School
In recent years, the Tsuruoka Police Station (Keigo Sato) has started the "Buy-by Accident Zero Operation" in an attempt to eliminate accidents involving bicycles and motorcycles, which occur frequently in the jurisdiction.
In addition to promoting accident prevention enlightenment with traffic safety organizations in the jurisdiction, we will start to strengthen the crackdown on bicycle traffic rule violations.
Three traffic fatal accidents occurred this year within the jurisdiction of the station, killing a person who was driving a motorcycle or bicycle.
Although the number of accidents is declining, the rate of bicycle-related accidents is about 11.7% as of June 30, and motorcycle-related accidents are about 5.8%, both higher than the prefecture average.
In particular, the rate of bicycle accidents in the past five years has exceeded the prefecture average in many years, and we planned a strategy to overcome this situation.
The name of the operation is "bike" and "bicycle" multiplied by the meaning of eradicating accidents.
We will ask related organizations to encourage the elderly to drive and use luminous reflectors more than ever in traffic safety classes.
At the same station, a yellow card (guidance warning slip) will be issued at the time of crackdowns to call attention.
The start ceremony of the operation was held on the 21st at the Shoko Gakuen Driving School in Tsuruoka City.
