Instantly detect the occurrence of a crisis from online information and judge hoaxes (JBpress) --Yahoo! News
"I want to know where and what kind of disaster or accident occurred as soon as possible!"
This is not limited to news media such as television and newspapers, but there is a strong need for many companies such as social infrastructure companies and local governments.
The service that responds to this is "Spectee," which was developed by Spectee, which handles information analysis using AI.
[Photo] An alert from Specty determines the authenticity of social media information by a specialized team.
Nowadays, the first means for people to know the occurrence of disasters and accidents is shifting from television to online information (social media).
Social media such as Twitter has become an important medium for disseminating information immediately after a disaster or accident occurs.
However, it is difficult to manually watch the overflowing information and extract useful information from it.
Specty has the function of detecting information related to natural disasters and accidents from information flowing on social media such as Twitter, Instagram, and Facebook, analyzing the content, determining the authenticity of the information, and then distributing it to the user company.
"A wide range of events with negative impacts that stop or stagnate social activities are regarded as" crises "" (Kenjiro Murakami, CEO), a crisis management support service that visualizes various crises occurring in Japan and overseas. That's right.
NHK at the time of the Kumamoto earthquake that occurred in April 2016 was the first major use case of Specty, and since then, the movement of recruitment has spread rapidly among companies.
It is said that not only news media such as TV stations and newspapers, but also companies that support social infrastructure such as electricity, gas and transportation, and more than 350 domestic companies such as local governments all over the country are currently using Specty.
■ Analyze posts to determine the type and location of the "crisis"
Specty distributes information in four steps: "collecting information", "analyzing and classifying", "titled", and "authenticity judgment".
The user company specifies in advance the area for collecting information (prefectures, cities, wards, towns and villages, etc.) and the category of crisis (disaster, accident, etc.).
Specty collects posts that meet that designation using an API provided by social media.
Then, the text, images, and videos contained in the collected posts are analyzed and classified.
For example, if there is a video showing a fire engine, black smoke rising from the building, and orange flames coming out of the room, it is classified as "fire".
In addition, images of overturned automobiles are classified as "traffic accidents", and images of flooded roads are classified as "road flooding".
Specty also estimates where disasters and accidents occur.
"I often don't know the location from the posts, so I'm estimating by combining various information," says Murakami.
For example, if a road sign or signboard is reflected in an image or video, the place name information is extracted from it and collated with the place name database to identify the place.
